<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">discompassionate</ENAMEX> and deluded rewriting of history, that <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lincoln</ENAMEX> was no <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">NAACP</ENAMEX>
poster <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">boy</ENAMEX> himself. He publicly declared on many occasions that <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">blacks</ENAMEX> would
never be the functional equals of <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">whites</ENAMEX> in intelligence, ability, creativity,
or social and economic skill, but that they must nevertheless be given their
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">freedom</ENAMEX> and some basic legal rights. He was never an <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">advocate</ENAMEX> of integration of
